office.description:
The Barbagelata name has been a part of San Francisco’s history since the late 1870s.  As the American dream came into fruition, our ancestors established their homes and businesses in North Beach and eventually moved to San Francisco's newly built Marina District. "Home, Sweet Home" included a home on Lombard and flats on Chestnut and Alhambra Streets for our family.   In 1952, John Barbagelata established Barbagelata & Company which became one of San Francisco’s leading real estate agencies from the late 1950s to the 1980s.  Paul and Anna Barbagelata kept the family business alive and thriving in the early 1990s. They currently maintain a staff of 40 agents with top market share in various neighborhoods and a Top 25 Bay Area Residential Real Estate ranking in the San Francisco Business Times.

We are proud to serve the local community and to provide a five star experience for many years to come.
